      "writtenOn": "2017-06-22T20:29:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we need to worry about the precision of %f? (Same for vec2 and vec4.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 170,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 170,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "4b08308cd10ac58ec51d5159b4bd0b7e17e70f42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0741c91e_370a07b9",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLCPPCodeGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 23
      },
      "lineNbr": 170,
      "author": {
        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-26T20:33:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m going to say \"probably not\". GPUs in general are pretty sloppy about floating point precision, we\u0027re often dealing with 16 or even 8 bit floats on the GPU, and the final answer we are coming up with (a color channel value) doesn\u0027t require a great deal of precision in the first place.\n\nWhile a round trip to and from %f could obviously slightly affect calculations, I don\u0027t think it\u0027s something to stress about for the time being.",
      "parentUuid": "b9215842_d91826c3",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 170,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 170,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "4b08308cd10ac58ec51d5159b4bd0b7e17e70f42",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
